        "eyebrow": "Patch Notes",
        "title": "Patch 6.84d",
        "description": "In this patch, we pursued several goals:<br /><br />1. <b>Hero Balance:</b> We weakened heroes that were too strong but tried not to 'kill' them while preserving their unique identity. We buffed weak heroes by studying winrate statistics and how these heroes were changed in nearby patches. Sometimes a hero is already decent but just needs a small boost to stay consistently strong and interesting.<br /><br />2. <b>Strengthening 'Lost' Heroes:</b> Some heroes feel unnecessary—as if they have no place in the current meta, and the longer the game goes, the harder it becomes for them to be useful. We significantly buffed these heroes in their interesting features—perhaps now they'll find their place and shine in new ways.<br /><br />3. <b>Quality of Life:</b> While you can argue for 'old school' dota with no room for casuals, some solutions are genuinely good: for example, buying Sentry Wards individually or reducing excessively long animations.",
